nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 38 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 39 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 460 mg
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
course: main course
cuisine: North America
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise (quarter any larger sprouts). Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve any larger carrots lengthwise first). Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Toss Brussels sprouts and carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @Italian Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and lightly browned, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with remaining Italian Seasoning, salt, and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> Press beef down with a #spatula{} to ensure even browning.

Turn off heat; transfer beef to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken or pork for beef. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-6 minutes per side, or cook pork to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

== Creamy Lemon Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef over medium heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Whisk in @water{1/3%cup}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Simmer, whisking, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat. Whisk in @Crème Fraîche{2%tablespoon}, @Butter{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of lemon zest until combined. Season with salt and pepper.

== Balsamic-Glazed Vegetables ==

Once veggies are done, transfer to a large #bowl{}. Add half the @Balsamic Glaze{5%teaspoon} and toss until evenly coated.

== To Serve ==

Slice beef crosswise.

> Slice chicken or pork against the grain.

Divide beef and veggies between plates. Spoon sauce over beef and sprinkle with as much remaining lemon zest as you like. Drizzle veggies with as much remaining balsamic glaze as you like and serve.